(44, 1, '2022-11-23 22:03:42', '2022-11-23 19:03:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These are the most popular programming languages according to the <a href=\"https://pypl.github.io/PYPL.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">PYPL index</a> and <a href=\"https://survey.stackoverflow.co/2022/#most-popular-technologies-language\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Stack Overflow’s Developer Survey 2022</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Position</strong></td><td><strong>PYPL ranking September 2022</strong></td><td><strong>Stack Overflow’s Developer Survey 2022</strong></td></tr><tr><td>#1</td><td>Python</td><td>JavaScript</td></tr><tr><td>#2</td><td>Java</td><td>HTML/CSS</td></tr><tr><td>#3</td><td>JavaScript</td><td>SQL</td></tr><tr><td>#4</td><td>C#</td><td>Python</td></tr><tr><td>#5</td><td>C/C++</td><td>TypeScript</td></tr><tr><td>#6</td><td>PHP</td><td>Java</td></tr><tr><td>#7</td><td>R</td><td>Bash/Shell</td></tr><tr><td>#8</td><td>TypeScript</td><td>C#</td></tr><tr><td>#9</td><td>Go</td><td>C++</td></tr><tr><td>#10</td><td>Swift</td><td>PHP</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The PYPL index is regularly updated, so this ranking might vary over time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Programming languages ranking 2022</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s take a closer look at the most used programming languages in 2022.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Python</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Python</strong> is an open source programming language, initially designed by the Dutch programmer Guido van Rossum in the late 1980s. The first version, Python 0.9.0, was released in 1991. It is <strong>powerful, user-friendly and easy to learn</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Python is used in many fields such as Machine Learning (ML), automation and scientific computing. It can also serve as a scripting language for web applications. Furthermore, there are diverse <strong>Python frameworks, like Django, TurboGears and Flask</strong>, that support developers in the development of complex applications.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: Python Software Foundation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: Python 3.10.6.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: ABC, Ada, ALGOL 68, APL, C, C++, CLU, Dylan, Haskell, Icon, Lisp, Modula-3, Perl, Standard ML and VB.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>JavaScript (JS)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>JavaScript is one of the core technologies of the </strong><a href=\"https://www.stackscale.com/blog/world-wide-web-anniversary/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>WWW</strong></a>, together with HTML and CSS. It was initially developed by the American computer programmer Brendan Eich, at Netscape, in 1995. It is a must-have among software developers and a great starting point for beginners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>JavaScript must not be confused with Java, although both of them have a C-like syntax and JS was designed with Java’s syntax and standard library in mind. JavaScript and Java are actually very different:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>JavaScript</strong></td><td><strong>Java</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dynamic.</td><td>Static.</td></tr><tr><td>Prototype-based.</td><td>Class-based.</td></tr><tr><td>Run on the web browser.</td><td>Run on the Java Virtual Machine (JVM).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: ECMAScript 2021.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: AWK, HyperTalk, Java, Scheme and Self.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Java</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Java</strong> was originally designed by the Canadian computer scientist James Gosling, while working at Sun Microsystems, in 1995. It is a particularly popular programming language for server-client web applications. Although it was initially released under proprietary license, it is currently available under GNU GPL 2.0-only license.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: Oracle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: Java SE 18.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: Ada 83, C#, C++, CLU, Eiffel, Lisp, Mesa, Modula-3, Oberon, Object Pascal, Objective-C, Smalltalk, Simula67 and UCSD Pascal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>HTML</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The markup language <strong>HTML</strong>, short for HyperText Markup Language, was initially designed by the British computer scientist Tim Berners-Lee in 1993. Used in combination with CSS and JavaScript, HTML is <strong>used by web browsers to compose visual web pages</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: WHATWG (Web Hypertext Application Technology Working Group).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: Living Standard 2022.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CSS</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>CSS</strong>, short for Cascading Style Sheets, is a style sheet language, developed by W3C in 1996. It is used to <strong>format documents written in HTML or XML</strong>. So, as well as HTML and JavaScript, it is a cornerstone of the WWW.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: W3C (World Wide Web Consortium).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: CSS 3.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>SQL</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>SQL</strong>, short for Structured Query Language, was initially designed by the American computer scientists Donald D. Chamberlin and Raymond F. Boyce in 1974. It is a declarative programming language used for <strong>data management</strong> in relational <a href=\"https://www.stackscale.com/blog/popular-database-management-systems/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">database management systems</a> (RDBMS).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MySQL, MariaDB and Microsoft SQL Server are some of the most popular RDBMS nowadays.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 32/WG 3.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: SQL:2016.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: Datalog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>C#</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>C# </strong>(C Sharp)is a general-purpose, object-oriented programming language, initially designed by the Danish software engineer Anders Hejlsberg, while working at Microsoft, in 2000. It is used for <strong>developing web services, web, mobile and desktop applications, and games</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was approved as an international standard by Ecma International in 2002 and ISO/IEC in 2003.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: C# 10.0.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: C++, Cω, Eiffel, F#, Haskell, Icon, J#, J++, Java, ML, Modula-3, Object Pascal, Scala and VB.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>C</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>C</strong> is a general-purpose programming language, originally designed by the American computer scientist Dennis Ritchie in the 1970s. It stands out for the efficiency of its code. C is widely used for developing system software, creating applications and on a wide range of computer architectures — from <a href=\"https://www.stackscale.com/blog/most-powerful-supercomputers-linux/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">supercomputers</a> to embedded systems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>C has diverse standards, ANSI C, ISO C and Standard C</strong>, software developers are encouraged to follow to ensure portability between compilers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: ANSI (American National Standards Institute) and ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC22/WG14.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: C 17.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: ALGOL 68, Assembly, B (BCPL, CPL), FORTRAN and PL/I.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>C++</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>C++</strong> was initially developed by the Danish computer&nbsp; scientist Bjarne Stroustrup in 1985, as an extension of C. It is often used in software infrastructure, desktop applications, servers, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This programming language is <strong>mostly implemented as a compiled language</strong>. Some of the C++ compilers are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GNU G++.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Intel C++ Compiler.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Microsoft Visual C++ (MSVC).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC22/WG21.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: C++ 20.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: Ada, ALGOL 68, C, CLU, ML, Mesa, Modula-2, Simula and Smalltalk.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>TypeScript</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>TypeScript</strong> is an open source programming language, first released in 2012 by Microsoft. It is designed for <strong>developing large applications, JavaScript applications for client-side and server-side execution</strong>, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: Microsoft.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: TypeScript 4.8.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: ActionScript, C#, Java and JavaScript.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>PHP</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>PHP</strong> is a scripting language intended for <strong>web development on the server side</strong>. It was initially designed by the Danish-Canadian programmer Rasmus Lerdorf in 1994-1995. It is also used for creating dynamic web page content and many other programming tasks such as robotic drone control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many popular Content Management Systems, such as WordPress, Drupal or Moodle, use PHP.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: PHP Development Team, Zend Technologies and PHP Foundation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: PHP 8.1.9.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: C, C++, Hack, HTML, Java, JavaScript, Perl and Tcl.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>R</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>R</strong> is a programming language, initially developed by the New Zealander statistician Ross Ihaka and the Canadian statistician Robert Gentleman in 1993. It is very <strong>popular in statistical computing and graphics</strong>, for performing data analysis and developing statistical software. It is available under GNU GPL v2.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: the R Core Team and the R Foundation for Statistical Computing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: R 4.2.1.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: Lisp, S and Scheme.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Bash/Shell</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The command language and Unix shell <strong>Bash is the GNU Project’s shell</strong>. It was designed as a free software replacement for the Bourne shell by the American programmer Brian Fox, in 1989. Since then, most <a href=\"https://www.stackscale.com/blog/popular-linux-distributions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Linux distributions</a> use it as the default login shell. It is available under GNU GPL v3 or later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: Chet Ramey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: Bash 5.1.16.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Go</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Go</strong> was initially designed by the Swiss computer scientist Robert Griesemer, the Canadian programmer Rob Pike and the American computer scientist Ken Thompson, while working at Google, in 2007. <strong>It was developed to improve programming productivity</strong>, maintaining useful characteristics of other languages already in use.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: The Go Authors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>:&nbsp; Go 1.19.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: Active Oberon, Alef, APL, BCPL, C, CSP, Limbo, Modula, Modula-2, Newsqueak, Oberon, Oberon-2, occam, Pascal and Smalltalk.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Swift</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Swift</strong> is an open source programming language, originally designed by Chris Lattner, Doug Gregor, John McCall, Ted Kremenek, Joe Groff and Apple Inc. It was created as a <strong>replacement for Objective-C for developing MacOS and iOS applications</strong>. This language presents a simpler syntax and includes modern programming languages theory concepts. It is available under Apache License 2.0.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Current developer</strong>: Apple Inc. and open source contributors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last stable release</strong>: Swift 5.6.2.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Influenced by</strong>: C#, CLU, D, Haskell, Objective-C, Python, Ruby and Rust.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the PYPL ranking, Python, Java and JavaScript also led the ranking of <a href=\"https://www.stackscale.com/blog/popular-programming-languages-2021/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">the most popular programming languages in 2021</a>. But, according to Stack Overflow’s 2021 Developer Survey, JavaScript, HTML/CSS and Python were last year’s top three programming languages among respondents.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Top 10 programming languages in 2022', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%d1%81%d0%b0%d0%bc%d1%8b%d0%b5-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%bf%d1%83%d0%bb%d1%8f%d1%80%d0%bd%d1%8b%d0%b5-%d1%8f%d0%b7%d1%8b%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%be%d0%b3%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%bc%d0%bc%d0%b8%d1%80%d0%be%d0%b2', '', '', '2022-11-23 22:15:23', '2022-11-23 19:15:23', '', 0, 'http://wordpress.test/?p=44', 0, 'post', '', 0),
